book("Discovering Biomolecular Mechanisms with Computational Biology", ["Frank Eisenhaber"], "Springer Science & Business Media", "2007-03-20", "This anthology presents critical reviews of methods and high-impact applications in computational biology that lead to results that non-bioinformaticians must also know to design efficient experimental research plans. Discovering Biomolecular Mechanisms with Computational Biology explores the methodology of translating sequence strings into biological knowledge and considers exemplary groundbreaking results such as unexpected enzyme discoveries. This book also summarizes non-trivial theoretical predictions for regulatory and metabolic networks that have received experimental confirmation.", "0387367470", "9780387367477", 152, ["Science"], "en", "http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Pygg7cIZTwIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api", 5, 1, "http://books.google.co.th/books?id=Pygg7cIZTwIC&pg=PA58&dq=Biology&hl=&cd=94&source=gbs_api", "https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Pygg7cIZTwIC&source=gbs_api").
