book("Introduction to Green Chemistry", ["Albert Matlack"], "CRC Press", "2001-04-03", "With roughly 5500 references, this book may be considered more of a treatise than a mere introduction to green chemistry. Using an unconventional approach, the author provides a broad but thorough review of the subject, covering traditional green chemistry topics such as catalysis, benign solvents, and alternative feedstocks before moving on to less frequently covered topics such as chemistry of longer wear and population and the environmental chemistry. Topics such as these highlight the importance of chemistry to everyday life and demonstrate the real benefits that wider exploitation of green chemistry can have for society.", "084930623X", "9780849306235", 632, ["Science"], "en", "http://books.google.com/books/content?id=gAQssnCnA48C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api", 5, 2, "http://books.google.co.th/books?id=gAQssnCnA48C&printsec=frontcover&dq=Chemistry&hl=&cd=185&source=gbs_api", "http://books.google.co.th/books?id=gAQssnCnA48C&dq=Chemistry&hl=&source=gbs_api").
