book("Discrete Mathematics Using a Computer", ["Cordelia Hall", "John O'Donnell"], "Springer Science & Business Media", "2000", "This volume offers a new, hands-on approach to teaching Discrete Mathematics. A simple functional language is used to allow students to experiment with mathematical notations which are traditionally difficult to pick up. This practical approach provides students with instant feedback and also allows lecturers to monitor progress easily. All the material needed to use the book will be available via ftp (the software is freely available and runs on Mac, PC and Unix platforms), including a special module which implements the concepts to be learned.No prior knowledge of Functional Programming is required: apart from List Comprehension (which is comprehensively covered in the text) everything the students need is either provided for them or can be picked up easily as they go along. An Instructors Guide will also be available on the WWW to help lecturers adapt existing courses.", "1852330899", "9781852330897", 362, ["Computer science"], "en", "http://books.google.com/books/content?id=yP4MJ36C4ZgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api", 3, 1, "http://books.google.co.th/books?id=yP4MJ36C4ZgC&pg=PA297&dq=Mathematics&hl=&cd=64&source=gbs_api", "http://books.google.co.th/books?id=yP4MJ36C4ZgC&dq=Mathematics&hl=&source=gbs_api").
book("Higher GCSE Mathematics", ["David Rayner"], "N/A", "2000", "Oxford's best-selling Revision and Practice books are renowned for their clear explanations and examples supported by a wealth of practice exercises and past examination questions that build students' confidence for the exams ahead.Building on the experience of earlier best-selling titles, David Rayner's new textbook provides valuable practice and challenging revision exercises for all students aiming for higher grades at GCSE.· Up-to-date curriculum coverage· New non-calculator work in line with curriculum changes· Clear explanations and worked examples· Numerous carefully constructed exercises and a section of ideas for longer investigations to encourage students to use and apply the mathematics they have learnt· Practice exam questions· Numerical answers to all questions", "0199147914", "9780199147915", 500, ["Mathematics"], "en", "http://books.google.com/books/content?id=fyOGm30cP30C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api", 3, 3, "http://books.google.co.th/books?id=fyOGm30cP30C&pg=PP5&dq=Mathematics&hl=&cd=65&source=gbs_api", "http://books.google.co.th/books?id=fyOGm30cP30C&dq=Mathematics&hl=&source=gbs_api").
book("A Modern Introduction to Ancient Indian Mathematics", ["T. S. Bhanu Murthy"], "New Age International", "1993", "The Purpose Of This Book Is To Draw The Attention Of Students And Teachers Of Mathematics To The Historical Continuity Of Indian Mathematics, Starting From The Sulba Sutras Of The Vedas Up To The 17Th Century. The Book Includes Proofs, Not Presented So Far, Of The Propositions Stated In The Well-Known Treatise Vedic Mathematics By Sri Bharati Krishna Teertha. It Also Introduces To The Modern Reader The Work Of Aryabhata, Brahmagupta, Bhaskara And Madhava.", "8122403719", "9788122403718", 230, ["Hindu mathematics"], "en", "http://books.google.com/books/content?id=R7cJuj1VEJ0C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api", 4, 1, "http://books.google.co.th/books?id=R7cJuj1VEJ0C&pg=PR8&dq=Mathematics&hl=&cd=66&source=gbs_api", "http://books.google.co.th/books?id=R7cJuj1VEJ0C&dq=Mathematics&hl=&source=gbs_api").
