book("Quantitative Techniques for Managerial Decisions", ["U. K. Srivastava", "G. V. Shenoy", "S. C. Sharma"], "New Age International", "1989", "This Book Is Designed To Serve As A Text For Management, Economics, Accountancy (Chartered And Cost Accountancy), And Commerce Students. The Book Covers Concepts, Illustrations And Problems In Statistics And Operations Research. Part I Deals With Statistical Techniques For Decision Making. Part Ii Studies Various Operations Research Techniques For Managerial Decisions.The Book Contains Illustrations And Problems, Drawn Extensively From Various Functional Areas Of Management, Viz., Production, Finance, Marketing And Personnel, Which Are Designed To Understand Real Life Decision Making Situations. In Order To Make The Book Self-Contained, All Relevant Mathematical Concepts And Their Applications Have Been Included. To Enhance The Understanding Of The Subject Matter By The Students Belonging To Different Disciplines, The Approach Adopted In This Book, Both In Statistics And Operations Research, Is Conceptional Rather Than Mathematical. Hence Complicated Mathematical Proofs Have Been Avoided.This Book Would Be An Ideal Reference To Executives, Computer Professionals, Industrial Engineers, Economic Planners And Social Scientists. The Other Books By The Same Authors Are: Operations Research For Management And Business Statistics.", "8122401899", "9788122401899", 962, ["Business & Economics"], "en", "http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7tNUu92d5PkC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api", 3, 8, "http://books.google.co.th/books?id=7tNUu92d5PkC&pg=PA721&dq=Programming&hl=&cd=17&source=gbs_api", "http://books.google.co.th/books?id=7tNUu92d5PkC&dq=Programming&hl=&source=gbs_api").
